Avro requires two schemas for resolution - a reader schema and a writer schema. 

The writer schema is included in the file. 

And you *can* parse the schema out of the file

    String filepath = ...;
    DataFileReader&lt;Void&gt; reader = new DataFileReader&lt;&gt;(Util.openSeekableFromFS(filepath),
        new GenericDatumReader&lt;&gt;());
    System.out.println(reader.getSchema().toString(true));

This is how [`java -jar avro-tools.jar getschema`](https://github.com/apache/avro/blob/branch-1.8/lang/java/tools/src/main/java/org/apache/avro/tool/DataFileGetSchemaTool.java) works

And you may need the [`Util.openSeekableFromFS`](https://github.com/apache/avro/blob/branch-1.8/lang/java/tools/src/main/java/org/apache/avro/tool/Util.java#L102-L111) method since it seems to be package private

